321 695 927 (                SMALL RESOLUTIONS IN CLAUSES 2-5) 927 SB
321 845 1187 (This paper presents resolutions for a number of small issues in clauses) 1187 SB
321 895 1196 (2 through 5 of the September edition of the working paper.  Each issue) 1196 SB
321 945 1140 (is independent of all the others; the issues are grouped in this paper) 1140 SB
321 995 554 (only for the sake of convenience.) 554 SB
321 1095 1171 (Many of these issues are editorial and are presented here primarily so) 1171 SB
321 1145 1272 (that the Core Language Working Group can examine and refine them prior) 1272 SB
321 1195 1195 (to the Hawaii meeting.  Proposals that the Core WG deems substantive) 1195 SB
321 1245 915 (will be presented as formal motions to the Committee.) 915 SB
321 1345 1680 (======================================================================) 1680 SB
321 1445 1023 (ISSUE 1: Partial preprocessing tokens and partial comments) 1023 SB
321 1545 416 (CURRENT WORDING:) 416 SB
321 1645 310 (    2.1 footnote 13:) 310 SB
321 1745 1099 (        A partial preprocessing token would arise from a source file) 1099 SB
321 1795 1095 (        ending in one or more characters of a multi-character token) 1095 SB
321 1845 1198 (        followed by a "line-splicing" backslash. A partial comment would) 1198 SB
321 1895 1167 (        arise from a source file ending with an unclosed /* comment, or) 1167 SB
321 1945 1106 (        a // comment line that ends with a "line-splicing" backslash.) 1106 SB
321 2045 435 (PROPOSED WORDING:) 435 SB
321 2145 310 (    2.1 footnote 13:) 310 SB
321 2245 1099 (        A partial preprocessing token would arise from a source file) 1099 SB
321 2295 955 (        ending in the first portion of a token that requires a) 955 SB
321 2345 1157 (        terminating sequence of characters, such as a header-name that) 1157 SB
321 2395 1119 (        is missing the closing " or >.  A partial comment would arise) 1119 SB
321 2445 1030 (        from a source file ending with an unclosed /* comment.) 1030 SB
321 2545 525 (RATIONALE FOR CHANGE:) 525 SB
321 2645 1206 (All the "spliced newlines" were removed in phase 2; consequently, they) 1206 SB
321 2695 1122 (cannot contribute to partial tokens in phase 3.  Similarly, there are) 1122 SB
321 2745 1170 (no partial // comments, because every source file is required to end in) 1170 SB
321 2795 381 (an unescaped newline.) 381 SB
321 2895 1680 (======================================================================) 1680 SB
