321 845 352 (    2.5p2 footnote 15:) 352 SB
321 945 1025 (        Thus the "stringized" values \(16.3.2\) of [ and <: will be) 1025 SB
321 995 1045 (        different, maintaining the source spelling, but the tokens) 1045 SB
321 1045 717 (        can otherwise be freely interchanged.) 717 SB
321 1145 525 (RATIONALE FOR CHANGE:) 525 SB
321 1245 1040 (The "behavior" of the two versions of the operator is identical) 1040 SB
