321 795 809 (ISSUE 7: Permissible locations for qualified-ids) 809 SB
321 895 416 (CURRENT WORDING:) 416 SB
321 995 215 (    3.4.3.1p1:) 215 SB
321 1095 1128 (        a class member can be referred to using a qualified-id as soon) 1128 SB
321 1145 999 (        as the member point of declaration \(3.3.1\) in the class) 999 SB
321 1195 836 (        member-specification has been encountered.) 836 SB
321 1295 151 (    5.1p8:) 151 SB
321 1395 1079 (        a class member can be used in a qualified-id as soon as the) 1079 SB
321 1445 1132 (        member's point of declaration \(3.3.1\) has been encountered in) 1132 SB
321 1495 618 (        the class member-specification.) 618 SB
321 1595 435 (PROPOSED WORDING:) 435 SB
321 1695 215 (    3.4.3.1p1:) 215 SB
321 1745 151 (    5.1p8:) 151 SB
321 1845 1106 (        a class member can be referred to using a qualified-id at any) 1106 SB
321 1895 669 (        point in its potential scope \(3.3.6\).) 669 SB
321 1995 525 (RATIONALE FOR CHANGE:) 525 SB
321 2095 1200 (By focusing exclusively on lexical ordering, the current wording leaves) 1200 SB
321 2145 1231 (open the question of whether forward references in the bodies of member) 1231 SB
321 2195 1048 (functions defined inside the class can be qualified or not.  The) 1048 SB
321 2245 1156 (revised wording makes clear that such forward references, as well as) 1156 SB
321 2295 1125 (any references in the class definition that lexically follow the point) 1125 SB
321 2345 882 (of declaration of the member, can use a qualified-id.) 882 SB
321 2445 1680 (======================================================================) 1680 SB
